# API Reference

> Bounded scope per endpoint. AI agents debugging endpoint behaviour
> retrieve this doc for a specific call site, not the whole catalog.

## Overview

> One paragraph: what this API does, the base URL pattern, the auth
> model. Cross-link to [`architecture.md`](./architecture.md) for
> system context.

## Conventions

* **HTTP methods.** Which verbs this API uses for which intents.
* **Error envelope.** Shape of error responses, status code → meaning.
* **Pagination.** Token / offset / cursor; default page size.
* **Content types.** Request / response media types.
* **Rate limits.** Per-token / per-IP, headers used to surface them.
* **Idempotency.** Which methods are idempotent, how retry-safety
  is communicated.

## Endpoints

> One subsection per endpoint OR per resource group. Each entry is
> AI-retrievable on its own.

### `<METHOD> <path>`

**Purpose.** One sentence.

**Auth.** What token / scope / role is required.

**Request.**

```http
<METHOD> <path>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "field": "value"
}
```

**Response.**

```json
{
  "ok": true
}
```

**Errors.** Status codes this endpoint can return and what causes each.

**Idempotency.** Safe to retry? Idempotency key required?

**Notes.** Edge cases, gotchas, version-specific behavior.

---

> Add new endpoints above. Keep each entry under 50 lines — agents
> retrieve one endpoint at a time; bounded scope matters.

